Subject: Problem with job offer for Puneet Mathur


Vince:

 This is regarding Puneet Mathur who we interviewed last week and decided to

make an offer to join the Retail research team. I called him to inquire about

his current compensation. His current base salary is $115,000 with a minimum

bonus of 20%. His last pay raise and bonus were in September 1999 and he is

expecting a raise and a bonus this September. The offer we would like to give

him ($85-90K base) is obviously way below his expectations. And I don't see

how we can offer him what he expects from us ($125K base - on par with mine),

as it would be placing him well above Ronnie & Osman who are definitely more

experienced and, in my view, more qualified. Let me know what to do.


Thanks,

Krishna.
